 HTML Learning Projects

 Overview

This repository contains a collection of HTML practice projects completed to develop my understanding of basic web development concepts. The exercises cover HTML document structure, headings, paragraphs, text formatting, comments, quotations, line breaks, and horizontal rules.

 Projects Included

My Daily Routine – A webpage describing my daily activities.
My Favorite Things – A page about my favorite foods, hobbies, and interests.
My Wonderful Parents – A webpage expressing appreciation for my parents.
The Importance of Education – An article page featuring a quote and citation.
Understanding HTML Comments – A project demonstrating the use of HTML comments.
Text Formatting Exercises – Practice with various text formatting elements.
Preformatted Text Exercise – Demonstrating the use of preformatted text.

 Skills Learned

 Creating structured HTML documents
 Using headings and paragraphs effectively
 Adding comments for code organization
 Working with quotations and citations
 Applying text formatting elements
 Using line breaks and horizontal rules

 Technologies Used

 HTML5
 Visual Studio Code

 Author

Mariam Mohammed Kasim

This repository showcases my progress in learning HTML and building a strong foundation in web development.
